  description: 'Across the northwestern provinces of the Roman Empire, from the mist-shrouded hills of Britannia to the river valleys of Gaul and Germania, archaeologists have unearthed more than a hundred and thirty small, hollow bronze objects — twelve-sided, riddled with holes of varying sizes, studded with knobs at every corner. No Roman text mentions them. No mosaic depicts them. No inscription explains them. After eighteen hundred years and more than fifty proposed theories, nobody knows what they were for. This is the story of archaeology\'s most beautiful enigma.',
